      "content": "Your perspective on feeling like you're just playing a role without an audience or purpose echoes the existentialist and nihilistic philosophies that acknowledge the indifference of the universe to human existence. It can be a profoundly isolating and numbing experience, especially when logic and reason seem to confirm the notion that our endeavors are ultimately inconsequential. This feeling can lead to a sense of emptiness and disconnection, which can be intense and all-consuming.",
      "source": "target",
